Hi Arvind,

For these type of questions, please use the Q&A first, JIRA is for bug reports and feature requests: http://developer.appcelerator.com/questions/newest

Anyway, can you go to "Titanium Studio -> Preferences... -> Studio -> Platforms -> iOS" and check that iOS SDK Home points to:

{code}/Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Developer/Platforms/iPhoneOS.platform/Developer/SDKs{code}

If not, please run this in Terminal:

{code}xcode-select --print-path{code}

Check that it points to:

{code}/Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Developer{code}

If not run:

{code}sudo xcode-select -switch /Applications/Xcode.app/Contents/Developer{code}
